                            <h2>Why Choose Cloud Hosting Over On-Premise Servers</h2>
                            <p>With cloud computing providing many advantages to the users, there is no rocket science in understanding why it has become the latest trend and is being adopted by a majority of enterprises globally. Both cloud computing and on-premise servers are computing technologies. However, before a company selects a technology it is first essential for them to understand the difference between the two.</p>
                            <p>At Biz4Group we help you to decide between the traditional on-premise infrastructure and cloud business model depending upon the scope and requirement of your project. As the force behind the  successful development of numerous <a href="https://www.biz4group.com/blog/why-security-and-privacy-control-are-crucial-while-implementing-an-ecommerce-solution" target="_blank"><b>eCommerce solutions,</b></a>  our developers at Biz4Group encourage the adoption of cloud infrastructure due to the following benefits: </p>
                            <h4>Cost</h4>
                            <p>On-premise infrastructure is comparatively costlier than cloud solutions and often needs a dedicated team of IT professionals for the management and upkeep of the system. Cloud hosting, on the other hand, brings perks such as infrastructure maintenance, data security, platform upgrades, and bug fixes.</p>
                            <h4>Security</h4>
                            <p>Data security offered by cloud hosting services can easily beat an on-premise server by a huge margin. With cloud-based services backing your eCommerce transactions, you can rest assured about the financial data and platform integrity.</p>
                            <h4>Almost Zero Downtime</h4>
                            <p>Server downtime directly affects the profitability of an eCommerce store and completely cut short revenues along with customer experience. By signing up with cloud hosting, your business store will experience more than 99% of uptime with little to no loss to the operations.</p>
                            <h4>Backup Processes</h4>
                            <p>With cloud hosting, your website data can be easily backed-up, either automatically or on-demand. With the availability of both onsite and off-site storage facilities, cloud hosting further improves store management and enhances disaster response strategies.</p>
                            <h4>On-Demand Scalability</h4>
                            <p>Scalability is AWS's biggest advantage. The AWS auto-scaling services automatically manage the capacity of resources as per the requirements. Cloud hosting brings along a myriad of functional benefits for your eCommerce platform which on-premise solutions fail to offer.</p>
