                            <h2>Why AWS Is Best for eCommerce Store Applications?</h2>
                            <p>Amazon Web services are cloud-based infrastructure-related applications that can easily be scaled and configured depending on the business requirement. Amazon is the world’s largest eCommerce company and understands the know-how of leading the market space. At Biz4Group we incorporate AWS services with our experience and expertise that allows your business platform to gain the competitive lead. Our services offer you technological precedence for better interaction, engagement, and sales prospects. </p>
                            <h2>AWS Architecture</h2>
                            <p>To simplify the roadmap to setting up an eCommerce platform, AWS cloud offers CloudFormation templates that can be integrated with just a few clicks. With the correct cloud configuration and architecture, your eCommerce business will always be ready to scale in situations of an unexpected surge.</p>
                            <h2>Handling traffic surge</h2>
                            <p>With conventional hosting solutions, numerous websites report sudden crashes during the peak shopping season. However, AWS services consist of scalability and make traffic handling a simplified process. The platform provides dynamic features which allow the allocation of resources as and when required.</p>
                            <h2>Data backup</h2>
                            <p>AWS is a world leader in providing cloud computing solutions to SMBs and large enterprises working in the eCommerce domain. Its ability to tackle situations, preventing system failures or server damages, ensure operational integrity, and much more enables smooth and error-free functioning of the servers at any given point in time.</p>
                            <h2>Security and Regulatory Compliance</h2>
                            <p>Our developers at Biz4Group incorporate the latest security measures along with AWS security certificates like Payment Cards Industry (PCI) and Data Security Standard (DSS). Moreover, the cloud architecture also comes with tools like web application firewalls, compliance ‘checkers,’ etc. to ensure the best security practices.</p>
                            <h2>Platform Compatibility</h2>
                            <p>Along with core product catalog and checkout services, the eCommerce platform hosted on the AWS cloud comes with inherent compatibility with nearly all the CMS available in the development realm. It also provides added support and SDKs for robust platforms like Ruby, Java, PHP, Node.js, and .Net.</p>
                            <h2>Availability of Nearest Datacentre</h2>
